t locations writable by the server process (unauthorized arbitrary file write). The file content is partially attacker-influenced.

**Patch**:  Fixed in v1.0.1 with (1) path-safe validation on sender_id (character whitelist plus rejection of the . and .. tokens) and (2) a defense-in-depth containment check in the Markdown writer that rejects any write resolving outside the memory root before any filesystem access, covering both the write and the append read-modify-write paths.

**Remediation**:  Upgrade to EverOS 1.0.1. There is no workaround for affected versions other than upgrading.", "ghsa_id": "GHSA-c795-2g9c-j48m", "github_reviewed_at": "2026-06-19T21:43:12Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-c795-2g9c-j48m", "identifiers": [{"type": "GHSA", "value": "GHSA-c795-2g9c-j48m"}], "nvd_published_at": null, "published_at": "2026-06-19T21:43:12Z", "references": ["https://github.com/EverMind-AI/EverOS/security/advisories/GHSA-c795-2g9c-j48m", "https://github.com/EverMind-AI/EverOS/releases/tag/v1.0.1", "https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-c795-2g9c-j48m"], "repository_advisory_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/EverMind-AI/EverOS/security-advisories/GHSA-c795-2g9c-j48m", "severity": "high", "source_code_location": "https://github.com/EverMind-AI/EverOS", "summary": "EverOS: Path traversal in EverOS /api/v1/memory/add via unvalidated sender_id", "type": "reviewed", "updated_at": "2026-06-19T21:43:15Z", "url": "https://api.github.com/advisories/GHSA-c795-2g9c-j48m", "vulnerabilities": [{"first_patched_version": "1.0.1", "package": {"ecosystem": "pip", "name": "everos"}, "vulnerable_functions": [], "vulnerable_version_range": "<= 1.0.0"}], "withdrawn_at": null}
